NOTICE:

not_kernel supports the following device:

r8q - Galaxy S20 FE

Unsupported:
bloomxq - Galaxy Z Flip 5G
f2q - Galaxy Z Fold2 5G

* these two don't even have proper twrp in xda.

x1q - Galaxy S20 5G
y2q - Galaxy S20+ 5G
z3q - Galaxy S20 Ultra
c1q - Galaxy Note 20
c2q - Galaxy Note 20 Ultra

* These two above use broadcom wifi which is broken, and my workaround doesnt work anymore

gts7l - Galaxy Tab S7 (LTE)
gts7lwifi - Galaxy Tab S7 (WIFI)
gts7xl - Galaxy Tab S7+ (LTE)
gts7xlwifi - Galaxy Tab S7+ (WIFI)

* I mean, i already dropped all others, why would i maintain the tabs, anyway the kernel is 100% functional for them tho

To build with workflows:
Just call the codename.yml and it will build the kernel for that phone/tablet.
